    <item nodeId="node-1859">
        <command xml:space="preserve">ask merchant about the proclamation</command>
        <result xml:space="preserve">"It always returns before dawn," Silk repeats. "Back to the crypt. I do not know what that tells you, witcher, but I suspect you do."

&gt;</result>
        <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
        <children><child nodeId="node-1860"></child>
        </children>
    </item>
    <item nodeId="node-1860">
        <command xml:space="preserve">go north</command>
        <result xml:space="preserve">
Castle Keep
The castle is old and smells of damp stone and old candles. Guards eye you at the gate but let you pass. They know the look of someone who has come about the contract. Inside, the keep is dim, the tapestries faded. Velerad's office is at the end of the main corridor.

Velerad is a heavyset man in his fifties with a soldier's posture and a bureaucrat's tired eyes. He sits behind a broad desk covered in papers.

A rolled map of the palace district lies on the corner of Velerad's desk.

A stiff parchment with Velerad's seal and the terms of the commission.

&gt;</result>
        <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
        <children><child nodeId="node-1861"></child>
        </children>
    </item>
    <item nodeId="node-1861">
        <command xml:space="preserve">examine map</command>
        <result xml:space="preserve">Velerad whistles to you, with a wierd face that translates to something like "You come here and the first thing you do is looking at my belongings?".

 

&gt;</result>
        <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
        <children><child nodeId="node-1862"></child>
        </children>
    </item>
    <item nodeId="node-1862">
        <command xml:space="preserve">examine map</command>
        <result xml:space="preserve">Velerad is not that happy. Is face is turning red. Maybe you should stop looking at his stuff before talking to him.

 

&gt;</result>
