You stand in front of the Old Narakort Inn, facing north. You spend a few seconds looking at the entrance, listening to the hubbub of voices. The Inn is full of people who may get the wrong impression of you. Farther down the street there is a smaller inn named The Fox, facing south. It is quite empty.

