        </children>
    </item>
    <item nodeId="node-1957">
        <command xml:space="preserve">go north</command>
        <result xml:space="preserve">
Castle Keep
The castle is old and smells of damp stone and old candles. Guards eye you at the gate but let you pass. They know the look of someone who has come about the contract. Inside, the keep is dim, the tapestries faded. Velerad's office is at the end of the main corridor.

Velerad is a heavyset man in his fifties with a soldier's posture and a bureaucrat's tired eyes. He sits behind a broad desk covered in papers.

A rolled map of the palace district lies on the corner of Velerad's desk.

A stiff parchment with Velerad's seal and the terms of the commission.

&gt;</result>
        <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
        <children><child nodeId="node-1958"></child>
        </children>
    </item>
    <item nodeId="node-1958">
        <command xml:space="preserve">examine map</command>
        <result xml:space="preserve">Velerad whistles to you, with a wierd face that translates to something like "You come here and the first thing you do is looking at my belongings?".

 

&gt;</result>
        <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
        <children><child nodeId="node-1959"></child>
        </children>
    </item>
    <item nodeId="node-1959">
        <command xml:space="preserve">examine map</command>
        <result xml:space="preserve">Velerad is not that happy. Is face is turning red. Maybe you should stop looking at his stuff before talking to him.

 

&gt;</result>
        <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
        <children><child nodeId="node-1960"></child>
        </children>
    </item>
    <item nodeId="node-1960">
        <command xml:space="preserve">examine map</command>
        <result xml:space="preserve">Velerad is like: "This piece of sh**"... Maybe you should ask him about the proclamation first before examining the map.

 

&gt;</result>
        <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    </item>
    <item nodeId="node-1961">
        <command xml:space="preserve">look wad</command>
        <result xml:space="preserve">You get closer and see that it is a proclamation, signed by Foltest, King of Temeria, Pontar and Mahakam... You might want to examine it further to read the details.

&gt;</result>
        <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
        <children><child nodeId="node-1962"></child>
        </children>
    </item>
    <item nodeId="node-1962">
        <command xml:space="preserve">look it</command>
        <result xml:space="preserve">You read the proclamation carefully:

"BY ORDER OF KING FOLTEST OF TEMERIA

Let it be known to all citizens of Wyzim and its surroundings:

The palace district is hereby forbidden to all persons, by penalty of death. None shall enter, none shall linger after dark.

A creature of unknown nature dwells within the old palace vaults. It is dangerous. It kills. Fourteen years have passed since the curse was laid and seven since it first stirred.

His Majesty King Foltest, in his mercy, forbids any attempt upon the creature's life.

His Majesty hereby calls upon any man of skill and knowledge, witcher, sorcerer, or wise man, who believes themselves capable of lifting the curse upon the creature, to present themselves before the castellan Velerad at Wyzim.

Any man or woman capable of lifting the curse without harm to the creature shall be rewarded handsomely by the crown with three thousand oren.

Those who attempt to destroy the creature instead of breaking the spell will be tried for treason."



You think about pulling it off in case you need to ask about it.


&gt;</result>
        <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    </item>
